        {
            "url": "https://ashertuil.bandcamp.com/album/automatism-2",
            "title": "Automatism",
            "artist": "asher tuil",
            "label": "Room40",
            "band_id": 1591214235,
            "classification": "paid",
            "tags": [
                "Experimental",
                "ambient",
                "drone",
                "lowercase",
                "microsound",
                "minimal",
                "minimalist",
                "room40",
                "texture",
                "Providence"
            ],
            "item_id": 779391092,
            "art_id": 4039458940,
            "is_preorder": false,
            "datePublished": "27 Jan 2023 00:00:00 GMT",
            "about": "From Asher\nIn producing these works I returned for the first time since moving to Providence, RI to a practice of going each day to locations in or around the city to record sounds. I tried to avoid the more urban sound environments and record near one of the many bodies of water or in larger parks and woods.\nReturning to my studio I worked with the sounds I had recorded by putting them through a resonant filter in short passages. During the first few days, I layered electronic sounds over them only, but as the project started to take shape I experimented with having broadcast sounds which I had been using in the far background of the initial pieces as a foreground element. The strains of music captured from the radio brought the compositions into focus as the varied sources of sound interacted.\nAs I reflected on composing the music for this album, I thought about what led me to make the choices I made and which of them seemed inevitable. I had begun by combining some of the sounds in my new locale with sounds produced in my studio in a more or less habitual manner and ended up with something that I hadn’t intended—crafting something but also allowing it to take its own shape.",
            "credits": "released January 27, 2023\nAutomatism was recorded by Asher Tuil during December of 2021 in Rhode Island.\nMastered by Lawrence English at Negative Space.",
            "license": "all rights reserved",
            "coverUrl_0": "https://f4.bcbits.com/img/a4039458940_0",
