            ],
            "item_id": 1583768476,
            "art_id": 1769952193,
            "is_preorder": false,
            "datePublished": "15 Apr 2016 00:00:00 GMT",
            "about": "'There is a tense of longing and regret, in which every step becomes delayed, revised, held back a little bit. The past and future are hypothesized...'\nTorpor - Chris Kraus\n'Over the pile of ancient trash, over the colorful rags and broken glass, drifts a tremor, a vibration, just like the hot air above a tin roof at noon...'\nRoadside Picnic - Arkady and Boris Strugatsky\n'The space inside the tower's needlelike brain now began to vibrate, began to seep down through its muscular steel interlacements into the ground. Whereupon the tower wrenched its iron soles free of the foundation, rocked back, and hinged off.'\nThe Bookmark - Sigizmund Krzhizhanovsky",
            "credits": "released April 15, 2016\nrecorded in east somerville, ma.\nearly spring, 2016.",
            "license": "all rights reserved",
            "coverUrl_0": "https://f4.bcbits.com/img/a1769952193_0",
